# Claude Code OAuth token — get one by running `claude setup-token` on your host.
# Lets the agent use your Claude subscription instead of an API key.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# Or use an Anthropic API key instead — uncomment and fill in:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# GitHub personal access token — the agent reads/manages Issues AND pushes its
# branch + opens the PR. Create a fine-grained token:
# https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
# Required repo permissions: Issues (R/W), Contents (R/W), Pull requests (R/W), Metadata (R)
GH_TOKEN=
# bffless project API key (X-API-Key). One key, two consumers:
#   - the j5s-dev MCP (.mcp.json reads it as ${BFFLESS_API_KEY})
#   - the handoff-api skill, to upload PR screenshots to handoff.j5s.dev
# NOTE: this is a full-access key — the autonomous agent can read AND mutate live
# j5s.dev resources.
BFFLESS_API_KEY=
